<P>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#FF0000">*If HTML and/or <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/ubbcode.html" target=_blank>UBB Code</A> are enabled, this means you can use HTML and/or UBB Code in your message.</FONT>
<br>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">barfadin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i know you do something with the /pause command but forget. please give an example with sup heal and cheal. thanks!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Adarii</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You cant stop them, but you can help catch them..<P>eg:<P>/cast 8 <-- where CHEAL resides<BR>/g CHEAL inc for < %T ><BR>/pause 5 <-- gives enough time for the gem to reset if there has been a fizz<BR>/cast 8 <-- recasts cheal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here's something worth knowing:<P>Furthermore, you can also use the /pause command on the same line as another social by separating the commands with a comma. Even though the pause command is specified first, it is executed AFTER the command on the same line.<P>For example:<P>/sit off<BR>/pause 100,/cast 1<BR>/sit on<P>...would have the same effect as the example above.  It is important to note that the comma can only be used to separate a /pause command from another, and MUST be specified first on the line.  <P><BR>(from the everquest online docs)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">canddari</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just remember the /pause 100 in Electrae's post means you cant interrupt your ch and cast another spell for 10 sek. So if your spell fizzels you still have to wait 10 sek before casting a new CH.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Phalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You can also catch a fizzle by adding text in between casts..for example:<P>/sit off<BR>/cast 8<BR>/g CH'ing %t<BR>/cast 8<P>This has helped me a great deal, especially since I never learned how to use pauses (timing).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lynet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I also cut down on movement fizzles by adding a quick sit to my macro:<P>/sit<BR>/sit off<BR>/g [clever text here]<BR>/pause 7,/cast 1<BR>/cast 1<P><BR>Lynet Beaumains, The Damosel Savage</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Feias</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quick note on pause timing.<P>Look at the spell and where it says delay (ex. 4) when you insert a pause put it in for 40.<P>The number you see in the spell description is in tenths of seconds.  So if it has a recast of 2.8 you need to use a /pause 28.<P>This is useful for:<BR>/sit off<BR>/cast 1<BR>/g Greater Healing on %T inc<BR>/pause 39<BR>/book 1<P>This is for standing up casting then sitting in one hot key.  Different things can be done to help prevent fizzle.  I prefer to just hit ALT and the number needed but adding an additional /cast 1 somewhere can't be bad.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You can recast during a pause.  You just can't use hotkeys.  You can use alt-spellGem#, /cast SpellGem#, and I think even mouse.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badany</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here is my Macro for Complete Heal:<P><BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">code:</font><HR><pre><BR>/sit off<BR>/g Complete Heal on  -  %T<BR>/pause 2, /cast 2<BR>/pause 90, /cast 2<BR>/sit on<BR></pre><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>That will catch a fizzle for ya!<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28272" TARGET=_blank>Badany Greatheal</A><BR>Templar of the Prime Healer Rodcet Nife<BR>Zebuxoruk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ever fizzled a CH 2 or even 3 times in a row? Are you SURE you need that 10 second pause in your macro?<P>my CH macro:<BR>/cast 3<BR>/groupsay Incoming Complete Heal for %T.<BR>/cast 3<BR>/emote wants %T to feel like a new %R. Incoming CH.<BR>/cast 3<P>The text messages usually seperates the /casts enough that it catches the fizzles. IMHO, CH is too important to lock yourself out for even 2 seconds, much less 10.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corinus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, another thing people are forgetting about pauses.  Pauses only lock you out of your socials, but not anything else.  You can still use abilities and cast spell gems.  You just can't use those abilities and spells through a macro.<P>Personally, I like this setup, though it doesn't catch fizzles.<P>/cast 3<BR>/pause 40, /g Complete Healing on %T in 10 seconds<BR>/g Complete Healing hitting in 5 seconds.<P>(There is roughly a half second delay in between lines)<BR>If I fizzle or something, I can always recast the Complete heal by pressing ALT-3 without waiting for the macro.    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><p>[This message has been edited by Corinus (edited 01-19-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Daynan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I always get this little smile on my face when my first Complete Heal fizzles and the second one automatically kicks in  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Haldraeger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Something much easier is to have CH gem icon as a hotkey next to CH macro for chain, so if you fizzle you just simply hit the real CH button. Much easier then making a complicated hotkey and works faster.<P>I usually have hotkey order as:<P>1)  Sit/Stand<BR>2) 30 second pause CH macro<BR>3) Complete Heal Icon/Gem<BR>4) 70 or 80 second pause for Slowed MOBs<BR>5) DA<BR>6) DB<P> Seven through ten dont matter (to me).<P><BR>Haldraeger<BR>60 Cleric of OOP.<BR>Saryrn Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Daynan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You should have an assist key too.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corinus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Haldraeger, why not just map Sit/Stand to another key, like 'S'?  It's a mappable command under Keyboard options.  Frees you up a Hot Key.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>Same for Book.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arblac</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have DA and DB in same hotkey to free up 1 hotkey for flexibility. Both will not cast if both are up and ready but if one is used the other will cast. I also don't tie up one for sitting and standing when there are alternate ways to do so but it's all in what you like and are comfortable with.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Haldraeger:<BR><B>Something much easier is to have CH gem icon as a hotkey next to CH macro for chain, so if you fizzle you just simply hit the real CH button. Much easier then making a complicated hotkey and works faster.<P>I usually have hotkey order as:<P>1)  Sit/Stand<BR>2) 30 second pause CH macro<BR>3) Complete Heal Icon/Gem<BR>4) 70 or 80 second pause for Slowed MOBs<BR>5) DA<BR>6) DB<P> Seven through ten dont matter (to me).<P><BR>Haldraeger<BR>60 Cleric of OOP.<BR>Saryrn Server</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P><P>------------------<BR>Arblac<BR>Mystic Companions Guild<BR>Level 56<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mambo Healums</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have one just for the Enchanter in the group.  It saves time having to retarget.<P>/tar Enchanter_getting_whacked_04<BR>/sit off<BR>/g Casting Remedy on %t<BR>/cast 3, /pause 10<BR>/cast 3<P>That's it.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
